-- South Africa’s Competition Tribunal Approves 4 Mergers
-- B y   H i l t o n   S h o n e
-- 2012-07-25T11:47:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/south-africa-s-competition-tribunal-approves-4-mergers-correct-.html
(Corrects name of regulator in headline and first
paragraph.)  South Africa ’s Competition Tribunal
approved four separate mergers today after concluding they
wouldn’t affect significantly competition in the industries
concerned.  The acquiring companies are  Redefine Properties Ltd. (RDF) ,
 Sanlam Ltd. (SLM)  unit Sanlam Private Equity, a unit of Super Group
Ltd. and a unit of  PSG Group Ltd. (PSG) , the Pretoria-based regulator
said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hilton Shone in Johannesburg at 
 hshone@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hilton Shone at 
 hshone@bloomberg.net  